Returns: The outcome of the update for the given request.
Parameters: The external request ID to lookup.
getRequestOutcome(java.lang.String).Description: Retrieve the outcome of updating the specified request. If the request ID was not part of the original update operation, this will throw an exception.

Returns: The set of all the external request IDs that were a part of the update operation.
getRequestIds().Description: Provides the set of all the request IDs that were used for the update. This set does not preserve the original order in which updates were performed or added to the RequestUpdateOutcomes object.

ClassDesc: Result delivered when requests are updated. Possible status codes include: @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_OK_E@ if all of the requests updated successfully. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_NETWORK_ERROR_OPERATION_FAILED_E@ if the update operation failed due to network error. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_REQUEST_UPDATE_PARTIAL_SUCCESS_E@ if only some of the updates could be successfully applied. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_REQUEST_UPDATE_TOTAL_FAILURE_E@ if all of the update operations failed with hard errors. Retrying will not change this result. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_CLIENT_RECONNECT_REQUIRED_E@ if the client needs to reconnect to the service to access this data. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR_E@ if an unexpected error occurred in the service.
